<doc id="905007" wikidata="Q5121900" url="?curid=905007" title="Mazgaon">
<text>Mazagaon, also spelled Mazgaon and Mazagon (Portuguese era Mazagão), and pronounced by the Christian Bombay East Indians as &#x27;Mazgon&#x27; or &#x27;Maz-a-gon&#x27; and Marathi-speakers as Mazhgav. It was one of the seven islands of Bombay. It is now a part of the Mumbai Metropolitan Area.

